      "text": [
        " رَجُلٍ قَالَ عَلَيَّ بَدَنَةٌ وَ لَمْ يُسَمِّ أَيْنَ يَنْحَرُهَا قَالَ \"إِنَّمَا اَلنَّحْرُ بِمِنًى يَقْسِمُهَا بَيْنَ اَلْمَسَاكِينِ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4306 - Aban narrated from Muhammad ibn Muslim, from Abu Ja'far Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as), regarding a man who said: \"I am obligated to offer a camel,\" but did not specify where it should be slaughtered.\nImam (as) said: \"The slaughtering is to be done at Mina, and it should be distributed among the needy.\""
        ]
      }
